narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: I would recommend the class to a student who has a great interest in economics. The class studied heavy economic concepts and works that would have not been fun for someone who is not serious about economics.
Yes, because it provides a strong basis for writing at Yale.
Very importabt tool for improving academic writing skills.
Definitely! The content is fascinating and I struggle to see where else a freshman could possibly find it except for hard-to-get-in-to upper-level seminars.

ENGL 114 16 is a seminar focused on presenting different views of capitalism while simultaneously promoting strong writing skills. I would recommend it as is has vastly improved my writing abilities and expanded my knowledge of capitalism.
